dismissalText.commentary: Denesh Ramdin lbw b Utseya 4 (7b 0x4 0x6) SR: 57.14

dismissalText.commentary: Runako Morton c †Taylor b Mupariwa 16 (45b 2x4 0x6) SR: 35.55

dismissalComment.html: good length delivery outside the off stump, nothing special there, Morton looking for easy runs ends up with a thick edge and Taylor behind the stumps takes a good low catch - Morton's uneasy stay at the crease comes to an end - Mupariwa with the breakthrough!

image.caption: Blessing Mahwire celebrates a wicket
image.longCaption: Blessing Mahwire celebrates a wicket, Zimbabwe v Sri Lanka, 1st Test,  Harare, May 8, 2004

dismissalText.commentary: Chris Gayle c †Taylor b Mahwire 49 (73b 7x4 0x6) SR: 67.12

dismissalComment.html: got'm! good length delivery, pitched close to the off stump line and shaping away ever-so-slightly, Gayle is sucked into driving straight and the edge is produced, Taylor dives across to his left and takes a fantastic low catch - that's a big wicket!

dismissalText.commentary: Denesh Ramdin lbw b Utseya 4 (7b 0x4 0x6) SR: 57.14

dismissalComment.html: Utseya continues to prosper! quicker delivery, this one grips the surface and turns in sharply from close to the off stump line, Ramdin plays down the wrong line and gets hit on the pad, beaten for pace there - umpire Bucknor after the customary delay adjudicates in favour of the bowler - West Indies three down!

dismissalComment.html: good length delivery on the middle and off stump line, Sarwan gets forward and lofts it away, looking to clear the man at deep midwicket, gets the height but not the distance and Coventry there in the deep judges it to perfection

dismissalComment.html: Lara departs! short of a good length delivery outside the off stump, Lara moves across a long way, gets under the ball and lifts it down to fine leg, Mahwire runs back and nicely settles under it

dismissalText.commentary: Shivnarine Chanderpaul c †Taylor b Chibhabha 46 (74b 2x4 0x6) SR: 62.16

dismissalComment.html: good length delivery outside the off stump, Chanderpaul plays away from his body, a lazy looking dab shot, faintest of edges and Taylor takes a fantastic catch, vital breakthrough! West Indies 6 down

dismissalText.commentary: Dwayne Smith b Chibhabha 30 (18b 0x4 3x6) SR: 166.66

dismissalComment.html: bowled'm! full and on the stumps, almost a yorker, Smith makes room - looking to go inside out over cover, but fails to make contact and the ball crashes into the woodwork, end of a fine innings

image.longCaption: Blessing Mahwire celebrates a wicket, Zimbabwe v Sri Lanka, 1st Test,  Harare, May 8, 2004

dismissalText.commentary: Jerome Taylor b Mahwire 6 (4b 1x4 0x6) SR: 150

dismissalComment.html: nine down! good length delivery on the stumps, Taylor makes room and swings hard but misses the target by miles and the ball clips the top of off stump, bit of confusion and the third umpire is called in to confirm

dismissalComment.html: got'm! good length delivery, drifting down the leg side, Rinke, looking to clip it away on the leg side opens the face of the bat bit too early and the ball spoons up off the leading edge, Bravo at point runs backwards and nicely shuffles under it, excellent take

dismissalText.commentary: Terry Duffin b Taylor 1 (15b 0x4 0x6) SR: 6.66

dismissalComment.html: bowled'm! follows up the short delivery with a fuller length delivery, hint of in swing and Duffin is beaten comprehensively, stumps are shattered and Taylor gets one more to his name - Zimbabwe two down

dismissalText.commentary: Chamu Chibhabha c †Ramdin b Bradshaw 67 (100b 8x4 0x6) SR: 67

dismissalComment.html: good length delivery, pitched outside the off stump and angling away further, Chibhabha drives away from his body, a tired looking shot, ball clips the outside edge and goes straight to Ramdin behind the stumps - end of a superb innings

dismissalText.commentary: Brendan Taylor b Taylor 0 (1b 0x4 0x6) SR: 0

dismissalComment.html: golden duck! good length delivery, the one that swings back into the right-hander, Taylor shoulders arms and the ball crashes into the stumps

dismissalText.commentary: Elton Chigumbura c Gayle b Edwards 13 (35b 2x4 0x6) SR: 37.14

dismissalComment.html: finally the breakthrough! pitched up and slanting away from the right-hander, Chigumbura is drawn forward into the drive and the edge is produced, ball goes straight to Gayle at first slip who takes it on the second attempt - end of a fine partnership
